A concise build-and-tune checklist

• Geometry:• Web parameters: \(N_r,\Delta r,r_0,a\).
• Barrier shells: \(N_\ell,\;f_\ell(r),\;\omega_{n,\ell},\;\phi_{n,\ell},\;a_{n,\ell}\).

• Physics:• Density law: \(\rho_{\text{eff}}(s) = \mathrm{clip}(\kappa/s,\rho_{\min},\rho_{\max})\), with \(\kappa = \sigma_{\text{target}}\frac{A_0}{V_0}\frac{1}{g}\).
• Phase bounds: \(\mathrm{Var}(\Phi)\le \sigma_\Phi^2\), \(\Delta \phi_{\text{mesh}}\le \Delta \phi_{\text{allow}}\).

• Safety interlocks:• Stress: \(\sigma_g(s)\le \sigma_{\text{allow}}\).
• Ground: \(P_{\text{ground}}(s)\le P_{\text{allow}}\).
• Energy: \(\mathcal{E}(t)\le \mathcal{E}_{\max}\).
• Barrier: \(\mathcal{B}_\Sigma \ge \mathcal{B}_{\text{safe}}\).
• Ethics gate: Deny operations outside transport/storage/restoration.

• Ops protocol:• Deploy cage, lock phases, verify interlocks.
• Execute scale change within \(s\)-envelope and density law.
• Hold stabilization until \(\mathcal{H}<\varepsilon_{\text{open}}\) and \(\mathrm{Var}(\Phi)\) is nominal.
• Exit by ramping barriers and confirming external environment readiness.



